title: Disable backups on Marshmallow
message:
Disable backups on Marshmallow

Backups automatically restore on new devices, which makes no sense for
the app. The only file stored on the device is the restore file.

title: Only show "backup script" option if addon.d folder exists, see notes
message:
Only show "backup script" option if addon.d folder exists, see notes

I'm making an assumption that the addon.d folder will exist
on Cyanogenmod installs, since smasher816's addition didn't
check for this. Otherwise, the copy was failing silently on my
stock Nexus 5.

title: Add addon.d script
message:
Add addon.d script

Add a menu item to create/remove an addon.d script. This will allow
people running custom roms to keep their kanji fix between updates,
instead of having to reinstall it each time /system is reflashed.

title: Fixed font replacement for Lollipop.
message:
Fixed font replacement for Lollipop.

Only affects fonts.xml - While the documentation for fonts.xml says it's
best practice to change both, I'd rather only change 1 if it has the
same end effect - so we're at less risk of breaking OTA updates.

title: Can now revert with no backup
message:
Can now revert with no backup

If there's no backup file, it uses the stock Android fallback_fonts.xml
file, stored in /res/raw. I plan on adding support for this when the
font
file is screwed up or customized too.
